      "title": "Elemental Analysis Solutions & Analytical Instruments | SPECTRO",
      "description": "SPECTRO is a global leading supplier of advanced analytical instruments like ICP, Arc Spark OES, and XRF spectrometers for precise elemental analysis of materials.",
      "text_excerpt": "Elemental Analysis Solutions & Analytical Instruments | SPECTRO\nYour browser is out of date. The site is optimized for IE 9 (not compatibility mode) and above, Chrome 29, Firefox 23 and Safari 6.0. If you can not update your browser you can still contact SPECTRO directly by\nclicking here\nSemiquantitative ICP-OES Analysis\nNew Quadrupole ICP-MS\nFast On-Site Analysis\nAnalysis of Alloys in Seconds\nMetal Analysis\nUp to 2X shorter measurement times\nRoutine Elemental Analysis\nMass Spectrometry\nSPECTRO\nAT A GLANCE\nA Global Leader in Advanced Elemental Analysis Solutions\nSPECTRO is one of the worldwide leading suppliers of advanced analytical instruments. Our technologies include\nOptical Emission Spectroscopy\nArc/Spark OES\n), Inductively Coupled Plasma Optical Emission Spectroscopy (\nICP-OES\nInductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry (\nICP-MS\nand\nX-ray Fluorescence (XRF) spectrometry\n, used for precise elemental analysis in industry,\nresearch and academia\nSPECTRO is a preferred manufacturer in many industries, such as metals, chemicals, petrochemicals, environmental, pharmaceuticals, geology, food and more. Our analytical solutions help achieve\naccurate\nreliable\n, and\nefficient elemental analysis\nfor a wide range of applications.\nGlobal Presence & Expertise:\nMore than 40 years of expertise in analytical innovation, with more than 50,000 spectrometers installed worldwide.\nPrecision & Reliability:\nOur instruments are engineered for the highest demands in elemental analysis, ensuring reliable results.\nInnovative Solutions:\nWe continuously advance our technologies to meet the evolving needs in industry, research, and academia.\nSPECTRO continues to set the standard in analytical instrumentation, delivering cutting-edge solutions for accurate elemental analysis worldwide.\nNEWS\nSPECTRO AI QUANT: Fast, Easy Semiquantitative ICP-OES Analysis for Modern Laboratories\nThe March edition of the SPECTRO newsletter \"What's New @SPECTRO\" has been released.\nThe December edition of the SPECTRO newsletter \"What's New @SPECTRO\" has been released.\nThe September edition of the SPECTRO newsletter \"What's New @SPECTRO\" has been released.\nWEBINARS & LIVE STREAMS\nUpcoming live webinars:\nMay 12\nElemental Analysis of Superalloys: Ensuring Performance in Extreme Applications\nPlease click the live webinar title above to access the registration page.\nUpcoming pre-recorded webinar streams:\nApril 27\n\"Improving the Precision and Accuracy of ICP-OES Analyses\"\nApril 30\n\"Advanced Handheld XRF Solutions for Mining, Environmental, and Compliance Applications\"\nMay 4\n\"Grade Search or Grade Control: Choosing the Right Method for Reliable Metal Verification\"\nMay 7\n\"SPECTROCUBE — Elemental Analysis of Petroleum Products, Liquid Fuels and Lubricants\"\nThe videos will be streamed on\nwww.spectro.com/livestream\n— at 10 AM EDT (4 PM CEST). Please click the live stream title above to add the event to your calendar!\nMacCMS"
    },
